T1  - Trust and Participation in Organizational Decision Making as Predictors of Satisfaction
AU  - Driscoll, James W.
Y1  - 1978/03/01
PY  - 1978
DA  - 1978/03/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255661
DO  - 10.5465/255661
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 44
EP  - 56
VL  - 21
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This study assesses the usefulness of trust and participation in decision making in predicting satisfaction among a college faculty. Organizational trust, a political assessment of hierarchical decision makers, best predicts overall satisfaction. The congruence between desired and perceived participation best predicts satisfaction with participation in decision making.
AB  - This study assesses the usefulness of trust and participation in decision making in predicting satisfaction among a college faculty. Organizational trust, a political assessment of hierarchical decision makers, best predicts overall satisfaction. The congruence between desired and perceived participation best predicts satisfaction with participation in decision making.
